==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[threed]]'', ''[[þred]]'', from Old English ''[[þræd|þrǽd]]'', ''[[ðræd|ðrǽd]]'', from common Germanic ''*thrēdu'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*treH₁-tu-'', from ''*terH₁-'' "rub, twist".  Near cognates include German ''[[Draht]]'' and Icelandic ''[[þráður]]''.

